# Rules are given on a table-by-table basis, beginning
# with the *<table> and ending with COMMIT.
# Rules are appended to a chain using the -A <chain> syntax.
# The default policy for a chain is given by the lines
# beginning with :<chain>. It is evaluated after rules, so
# it only applies if there were not any matches.
*nat
:POSTROUTING DROP [0:0]
-A POSTROUTING -o wlan0 -j MASQUERADE
COMMIT
*filter
:FORWARD <action> [0:0]
-A FORWARD -i eth0 -o wlan0 -j ACCEPT
-A FORWARD -i wlan0 -o eth0 -m conntrack --ctstate
RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j <action>
COMMIT

